# Cloudflare Jobs Fetcher

## Purpose

Implement or modify the Cloudflare jobs flow used by this codebase:

- Backend fetches and filters jobs in `/api/cloudflare/open-positions`.
- Frontend fetches that endpoint and renders cards in `public/app.js`.
- Output shape must stay compatible with `renderCloudflareJobs`.

## Use When

- The user asks to fetch Cloudflare openings in this project.
- The user wants to change location or title matching rules.
- The user wants changes reflected in the dashboard metrics and cards.
- The user reports UI breakage after Cloudflare response shape changes.

## Inputs

- locationFilter: String used by backend for case-insensitive matching.
- titleRegex: Regex for matching role titles.
- titleFilters: String list returned in response metadata.

Default filters:

- locationFilter: lisbon, portugal
- titleRegex: /\b(ai|data)\b/i
- titleFilters: ["ai", "data"]

## Data Source

Use the same source as the backend route:

https://boards-api.greenhouse.io/v1/boards/cloudflare/departments/?render_as=tree

## Workflow

1. Fetch Cloudflare departments tree from Greenhouse.
2. Flatten nested departments into a single jobs list with `flattenDepartments`.
3. Resolve job locations with `getJobPostingLocations` from metadata first, then fallback to `job.location.name`.
4. Normalize each job exactly as backend expects:
   - id
   - title
   - url
   - postingLocations
   - location
   - firstPublished
5. Filter jobs where:
   - any posting location includes the locationFilter string, and
   - titleRegex matches title.
6. Sort by firstPublished descending.
7. Return response shape compatible with frontend rendering.

## Repo Contracts

- Backend route: `/api/cloudflare/open-positions` in `server.js`.
- Frontend fetch caller: `fetchCloudflareJobs` in `public/app.js`.
- Frontend renderer: `renderCloudflareJobs` in `public/app.js`.

Do not remove or rename these response keys without updating frontend code:

- ok
- source
- filters
- fetchedAt
- totalFetched
- totalMatching
- jobs

## Output Contract

Return JSON with this shape:

{
  "ok": true,
  "source": "https://www.cloudflare.com/en-gb/careers/jobs/?location=Lisbon%2C+Portugal&title=ai",
  "filters": {
    "location": "Lisbon, Portugal",
    "title": ["ai", "data"]
  },
  "totalFetched": 0,
  "totalMatching": 0,
  "fetchedAt": "ISO-8601",
  "jobs": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "title": "",
      "location": "",
      "url": "",
      "postingLocations": [],
      "firstPublished": ""
    }
  ]
}

If fetch fails, return:

{
  "ok": false,
  "error": "Failed to fetch Cloudflare jobs feed.",
  "detail": {
    "status": 0,
    "statusText": "",
    "data": ""
  }
}

## Notes

- Keep filtering case-insensitive.
- Keep output field names aligned with `public/app.js`.
- `renderCloudflareJobs` expects job fields `url`, `title`, `location`, and `firstPublished`.
- Preserve `totalMatching` because it is used in activity logs and dashboard metrics.
